</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>Legal requirements </strong>- Refer to obligations enforced by law. These encompass a wide array of laws, such as criminal law, civil law, and administrative law, which must be adhered to by individuals and organisations. Legal compliance ensures that entities operate within the boundaries set by the government.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Statutory requirements</strong> - These are specific obligations imposed by statutes, which are formal written laws enacted by legislative bodies. For instance, the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974 is a statutory requirement that mandates employers to ensure the health and safety of their employees.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">The differences between legal and statutory requirements</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Source of authority</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-43_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>Legal requirements </strong>- Derived from a broader spectrum of laws, including common law and statutory law.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-46_ pf-text-1"><strong>Statutory requirements</strong> - Specifically emanate from statutes passed by legislative bodies.
